welcome to stanford biofilm research center the stanford biofilm research center is a campus wide research facility for studies on microbial biofilms and houses an upright leica confocal microscope we have the ability to work with many different systems the upright scanhead and water immersion objectives allow imaging of films without removal from growing media this allows you to set up your experiments here in our facility and image real time in situ researchers both on and off campus are encouraged to use the imaging facility please contact lori howe for questions regarding scheduling fees or training click for info location the facility is located on the second floor of the james h clark building in room e 281 contact lori howe for details stanford university homepage home new users scheduling fees publications leica reference scope resources scope specifications contact us copyright 2001 2005 stanford biofilm research center all rights reserved last update march 28 2005
